"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46991","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-14","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not collect information about Gift Aid claimed by, or paid to, charities in respect of admission fees to view charity property, except for charities subject to enquiry. It would be administratively burdensome for charities to routinely provide a detailed breakdown of their income with every Gift Aid claim they make.</p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-04-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46991/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46991/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-03","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether HM Revenue and Customs keeps records of the amount of Gift Aid claimed by, or paid to, attractions in respect of qualifying admission fees paid to view charity property; and, if so, in what form the records are kept.","false","Biography information for Lord Lee of Trafford",,"Lord Lee of Trafford","HL6599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46992","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-04-14","<p>Our assessment is that unlawful incursions into British Gibraltar Territorial Waters by Spanish State vessels are a futile attempt to assert Spain's legal position in respect of the waters. Incursions are a violation of sovereignty, not a threat to it. They do not weaken or undermine the legal basis in international law for British sovereignty over Gibraltar, including British Gibraltar Territorial Waters.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-04-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46992/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46992/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-04-03","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the reasons the government of Spain has given for sending warships and other state vessels into territorial waters around Gibraltar.","false","Biography information for Lord Patten",,"Lord Patten","HL6600"
