k/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/256886/table11-1b.pdf</a></p><p>[2]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/277459/Table_2.6.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/277459/Table_2.6.pdf</a></p><p>[3]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/294267/20140312_Feb_v0.2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/294267/20140312_Feb_v0.2.pdf</a></p><p>[4]<a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/budget2012/excheq-income-tax-2042.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/budget2012/excheq-income-tax-2042.pdf</a></p><p>[5]<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/analysis-of-the-dynamic-effects-of-corporation-tax-reductions" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/analysis-of-the-dynamic-effects-of-corporation-tax-reductions</a></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton","HL6619","2014-04-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47012/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47012/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-03","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether there is any evidence that income tax and corporate tax revenues have increased as the rates of income and corporate taxes have decreased since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL6620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47309","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The UK's bilateral programme in the Occupied Palestinian Territories is helping to build Palestinian institutions, promote economic growth and support the most vulnerable Palestinians. Absent meaningful action from Israel to ease movement and access restrictions, however, our progress will always be limited.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47309/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47309/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what progress her Department has made on its programmes in Palestine.","false","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","903626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47810","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>I spent most of last week in Bangladesh, assessing the progress that has been made one year on from the tragedy of Rana Plaza. Steps have been taken to improve working conditions in the garment sector, including through factory inspections and strengthening the labour inspection regime. The UK's support is focused on all areas where action is needed: improving building safety and working conditions, empowering workers and urging buyers to take responsibility for their supply chains.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47810/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47810/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of international efforts to improve levels of safety and conditions of work in Bangladesh's garment industry.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","903622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47811","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>FGM is violence against women and girls. The UK has made the largest donor commitment ever to help end FGM, with a flagship programme of £35 million in at least 17 countries.</p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister will host a summit in July which will step up global efforts to end both FGM and child, early and forced marriage within a generation.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47811/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47811/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to tackle female genital mutilation and early and forced marriage worldwide.","false","Biography information for Jason McCartney","Colne Valley","Jason McCartney","903621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47812","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK is committed to ensuring all children, with a focus on the most marginalised and those with disabilities have access to education institutions and complete a full cycle of quality education. We are working with partners, such as UNICEF and UNESCO Institute for Statistics, to improve data for monitoring purposes.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47812/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47812/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that all the education programmes it funds are inclusive of children with disabilities; and what monitoring her Department undertakes to ensure that all such programmes include accessible materials for use by children with disabilities.","false","Biography information for Lord Blunkett","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Mr David Blunkett","903627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47813","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>Sri Lanka has met Millennium Development Goal No 1 which calls for the halving of extreme poverty, and is on track to meet most other MDGs. Poverty remains in areas of northern and eastern Sri Lanka where large numbers of Tamils live<strong>. </strong>We do not have a breakdown by ethnic group.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47813/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47813/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the levels of poverty among Tamils living in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","903625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47814","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The UN estimates that 9.3 million people are in dire need of humanitarian aid within Syria. At least 6.5 million people in Syria have been forced to flee their homes to other areas of the country and there are now over 2.6 million refugees in the region.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47814/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47814/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the humanitarian situation in Syria.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","903624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47815","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The Government welcomes the IPCC report. Climate change poses very serious consequences to human health, global food security, and can slow economic growth. Its impacts will be an extra burden for those living in poverty, and make it harder to reduce poverty in developing countries.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47815/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47815/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of conclusions of the recent UN IPCC report on the effects of climate change on developing countries.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","903623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46439","Attorney General","false","2014-04-07","<p>I have done so today.</p>","Beaconsfield","Mr Dominic Grieve",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46439/answer","Biography information for Mr Dominic Grieve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46439/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, when he expects to answer question No. 191801 tabled by the Rt hon. Member for Leeds Central on 12 March 2014.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46440","Attorney General","false","2014-04-07","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) has mandatory training for all prosecutors on cybercrime and specific training for prosecutors on offences under the Computer Misuse Act 1990. This supports guidance for prosecutors on the range of offences which can be committed through the use of cyber technology.</p><p>In addition, the CPS will soon be introducing new consolidated guidance for prosecutors on cyber-offending and a new package of e-learning for prosecutors in relation to cybercrime which will cover: digital evidence gathering; online grooming; online fraud; and, social media.</p><p> </p>","Beaconsfield","Mr Dominic Grieve",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46440/answer","Biography information for Mr Dominic Grieve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46440/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what recent assessment he has made of the cyber security crime skills of staff of the Crown Prosecution Service.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","194951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46441","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The licence expired on 4<sup>th</sup> May 2012. Temporary export licences are issued for a period of 12 months, with a condition that the goods are returned to the UK within the validity of the licence. The goods were returned to the UK on 23 May 2011.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46441/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46441/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when the standard individual export licence granted in May 2011 to permit tear gas ammunition to be exported to Turkey expired.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","195000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46442","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>In 2012, the median gross hourly wage for an Apprentice in England was £6.09. The mean was £6.21. In 2011, the equivalent gross hourly wages were £5.83 and £5.80.</p><p> </p><p>For females, in 2011, the median gross hourly wage was £5.96 and the mean £5.88. In 2012, these were £6.19 and £6.23 respectively.</p><p> </p><p>For males, in 2011, the median gross hourly wage was £5.43 and the mean £5.71. In 2012, these were £5.93 and £6.19 respectively.</p><p> </p><p>Please note that the only available data we have for Apprenticeship Pay is for 2012 and 2011, from the two Apprenticeship Pay Surveys (APS). These surveys do not calculate an annual wage from the survey responses as the hours Apprentices work are variable. There was a pay survey conducted in 2007, but this is not considered to be comparable with the two later years.</p><p> </p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeship-pay-survey-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeship-pay-survey-2012</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46442/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46442/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46442/answer/previousversion/5033","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the (a) median and (b) mean (i) annual and (ii) hourly salary is for (A) men and (B) women in Government-sponsored apprenticeship schemes; and what those figures were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","195007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46443","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The licence granted in May 2011 was for temporary export of &quot;inert tear gas/irritant ammunition&quot; for exhibition purposes. It was a condition of the licence that the goods were returned to the UK within 12 months and they were returned on 13 May 2013 .The licence did not authorise the export of any tear gas or &quot;live&quot; tear gas ammunition.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46443/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46443/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will investigate whether any tear gas exported to Turkey under the standard individual export licence granted in May 2011 was used on demonstrators in Turkey in 2013.","false","Biography information for Katy Clark","North Ayrshire and Arran","Katy Clark","195001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46444","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>Statistics are not available on applicants to part-time higher education courses as there is no centralised application service for part-time study. However, statistics on entrants to part-time courses at UK Higher Education Institutions (HEIs) are available from the Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) and have been provided back to the academic year 2004/05 in the following table.</p><p> </p><p>Information on enrolments at UK HEIs in the academic year 2013/14 will become available from HESA in January 2015.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Entrants<sup>(1) </sup>part-time courses by level of study</strong></p><p>Academic years 2004/05 to 2012/13</p><p>UK Higher Education Institutions</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>2004/05</p></td><td><p>2005/06</p></td><td><p>2006/07</p></td><td><p>2007/08</p></td><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Postgraduate part-time</p></td><td><p>108,920</p></td><td><p>113,955</p></td><td><p>116,215</p></td><td><p>116,320</p></td><td><p>128,945</p></td><td><p>132,745</p></td><td><p>127,925</p></td><td><p>109,535</p></td><td><p>102,190</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Undergraduate part-time</p></td><td><p>317,785</p></td><td><p>336,415</p></td><td><p>341,030</p></td><td><p>331,950</p></td><td><p>344,475</p></td><td><p>335,050</p></td><td><p>301,490</p></td><td><p>278,575</p></td><td><p>199,905</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total part-time</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>426,710</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>450,370</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>457,245</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>448,275</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>473,420</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>467,795</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>429,415</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>388,115</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>302,095</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Source: Higher Education Statistics Agency</strong></p><p><strong>Note:</strong></p><p><strong>(1) </strong><strong>Entrants refer to those students entering their first year of study. </strong></p><p><strong>(2) </strong><strong>Includes entrants from all domiciles (UK, EU and other overseas countries)</strong></p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46444/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46444/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people have applied for part-time higher education courses each year since 2004.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","195002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46445","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>Information on the number of apprenticeship achievements by age are published in a supplementary table to the Statistical First Release:</p><p><a title="blocked::https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2</a><br> <br><a title="blocked::https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/296345/apprenticeship-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xlsm" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/296345/apprenticeship-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xlsm" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/296345/apprenticeship-achievements-by-geography-learner-demographics-and-sector-subject-area.xlsm</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46445/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46445/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people who are (a) under 18, (b) 18 to 21 and (c) 22 or over have completed an apprenticeship in each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","195016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46446","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-07","<p>The Annual Survey of Hours and Earnings (ASHE), carried out in April each year, is the most comprehensive source of earnings information in the United Kingdom. Hourly levels of earnings are estimated from ASHE, and are provided by the Office for National Statistics for employees on adult rates of pay, whose earnings for the survey pay period were not affected by absence.</p><p> </p><p>Estimates for the number and proportion of national minimum wage jobs at sub-Regional geographies such as parliamentary constituency are not available for reasons of quality.</p><p> </p><p>Related information is available in the National Minimum Wage Low Pay Commission Report 2014, which contains some estimates for minimum wage jobs, as defined above, by Regions, gender and full-time/part-time:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/288841/The_National_Minimum_Wage_LPC_Report_2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/288841/The_National_Minimum_Wage_LPC_Report_2014.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46446/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46446/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many and what proportion of (a) people, (b) men and (c) women were in (i) work, (ii) full-time work and (iii) part-time work in each constituency earn the national minimum wage; and what those figures were in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","195026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46447","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The criteria for support from the Manufacturing Advisory Service (MAS) do not include any reference to state aid restrictions related to Common Agricultural Policy payments. MAS delivers support to manufacturers, and is able to support land based enterprises such as farmers, which have formally diversified their agricultural business from their product manufacturing activities.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46447/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46447/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 12 March 2014, Official Report, columns 595-6W, on public sector: food, whether the Manufacturing Advisory Service is unable to give grant aid to the farming industry due to state aid restrictions relating to existing Common Agricultural Policy payments.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","195018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46448","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-07","<p>Companies House cannot identify the number of new businesses registered in each constituency, as there is no central register of businesses.</p><p> </p><p>Companies House does have a register of companies but information on companies registered in each constituency could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46448/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46448/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many businesses are registered in each constituency; and how many businesses were so registered in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","195028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46449","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-07","<p>There is no central register of businesses. Companies House does have a register of companies but it cannot determine the number of companies classified as small and medium sized as defined by the Companies Act 2006. Information on companies registered in each parliamentary constituency could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46449/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46449/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many and what proportion of small and medium-sized businesses were registered in each parliamentary constituency; and what the equivalent figures were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","195022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46450","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>We plan to publish the responses received (unless they may be deemed confidential within the Freedom of Information Act's Code of Practice for authorities) alongside the Government's response to the views received.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46450/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46450/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish a summary of the responses to the consultation on strengthening the regulatory regime and fee structure for insolvency practitioners which closed on 28 March 2014.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46451","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>In March 2014 there were 20 people working on trade and investment (18.9 Full Time Equivalent FTE) in Turkey. This figure was not materially different in either May 2010 or Dec 2013.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46451/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46451/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many UK Trade & Investment staff were based in Turkey in (a) May 2010, (b) December 2013 and (c) March 2014.","false","Biography information for Nick de Bois","Enfield North","Nick de Bois","194830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46452","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>In October 2013, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office conducted an assessment to identify the prospects for UK export expansion to Turkey. The report concluded that UK exports to Turkey are projected to increase from £4.9 billion in 2011 to £9 billion in 2020. The report also identified which sectors provided the greatest opportunities and are most critical to growing UK exports to Turkey. UK Trade and Investment is leading for Government in actively helping UK business to maximise opportunities.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46452/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46452/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the prospects for UK exporters to Turkey; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nick de Bois","Enfield North","Nick de Bois","194834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46453","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The proposals in the consultation on the introduction of a Land Registry service delivery company are being considered against the option of remaining as is, and no decisions will be taken until all responses have been considered. As part of considering the consultation responses Government will be considering potential effects on interested parties (including conveyancers and small and medium-sized enterprises.)</p><p> </p><p>The way in which some Land Registry services are delivered will likely change as a result of the implementation of the Business Strategy. Land Registry will engage with customers as and when it introduces new services.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46453/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46453/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect on (a) conveyancers and (b) small and medium-sized enterprises of a change in the Land Registry's trading status to a Government Owned Company and implementation of the Land Registry plans for e-Mandation and self-service.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46454","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>We are aiming to publish the Government response within 12 weeks of the consultation closing, in line with the consultation principles.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46454/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46454/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he intends to respond to the consultation on the introduction of a Land Registry service delivery company.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46455","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The Government consultation on the introduction of a Land Registry service delivery company was sent to trade unions. Their responses, together with all other responses, will be considered as part of the decision making process.</p><p> </p><p>Land Registry management will engage with their trade unions on changes that may affect staff as a result of the consultation.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46455/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46455/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether trade unions will be consulted before a final decision on the future status of the Land Registry is made.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46456","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>We are currently considering all consultation responses. The Government response to the consultation will set out the main issues raised by respondents and how the Government intends to address these issues.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46456/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46456/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many responses he has received to the consultation on the introduction of a Land Registry service delivery company; and how many of those were in favour of the proposals.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46457","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-07","<p>We are currently analysing responses to the Government's discussion paper on building a more responsible payment culture and will publish the response shortly.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46457/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46457/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he expects to publish his Department's response to the consultation on Building a responsible payment culture.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","194885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46458","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>Ministers in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills meet with officials from the Insolvency Service on a regular basis to discuss a wide variety of insolvency issues.</p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46458/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46458/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when Ministers in his Department met officials from the Insolvency Service to discuss insolvency practitioner (a) fees and (b) partial licences in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","194873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46459","Cabinet Office","false","2014-04-07","<p>In July 2013 we published a One Year On report that gave a frank account of progress against the Civil Service Reform Plan. This is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/civil-service-reform-plan-one-year-on--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/civil-service-reform-plan-one-year-on--2</a>:</p><p>I took the opportunity to update the House on progress during the backbench debate on Civil Service Reform on 3 April 2014 and will update the House further in our Two Years On report this summer.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46459/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46459/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress he has made on reform of the Civil Service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","194874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46460","Cabinet Office","false","2014-04-07","<p>The Voting Membership of the Main Honours Committee comprises Head of the Civil Service (Chair); Chairs of the 9 Honours Committees; Chief of the Defence Staff; Permanent Secretary of the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office; another Permanent Secretary; Cabinet Secretary and a representative from the Prime Minister's Office. Membershipfor the past five years is set out below. Current membership of all honours committees is available at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/honours-committees" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/honours-committees</a>.</p><p>A copy of the table listing the Membership of the committee over the last 5 years will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46460/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46460/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will list the members of the Honours Committee in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","194884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46461","Cabinet Office","false","2014-04-07","<p>570 local authorities have completed compliance.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46461/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46461/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many local authorities have adopted the Government's public service network to date.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","194950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46462","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p> </p><p>The value of additional payments made as a result of appeals is £17,023.61. This is 0.0019% of the total value paid by the Scheme to date.</p><p> </p><p>Two annuitants have made successful appeals, and the total value of the payments made to them will depend on the duration on their annuity.</p><p> </p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46462/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46462/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total amount is in additional payments made by the Equitable Life payment scheme as a result of successful appeals to date; and what proportion that amount is of the total compensation awarded.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","194938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46463","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>Out of the over 800,000 payments that have been made, a total of 495 cases have been submitted to the Independent Review Panel to date. 477 have been resolved and 18 are in the process of being resolved.</p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46463/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46463/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many appeals made to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme (a) have been decided and (b) are awaiting resolution.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","194935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46464","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>Out of the 9 successful appeals by non-annuitants following receipt of new input data, the highest, lowest and average additional payments were: <br><br>a) £5,230.31<br>b) £32.91<br>c) £1,891.51<br><br>In addition two annuitants have made successful appeals. The total value of the payments made to them will depend on the duration on their annuity.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46464/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46464/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the (a) highest, (b) lowest and (c) average additional award paid following a successful appeal made to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme is.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","194936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46466","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>I have written to the Northern Ireland Minister for Finance and Personnel setting out that the Treasury will reduce Northern Ireland Executive budgets to reflect savings foregone as a result of the lack of progress on welfare reforms already in place in the rest of the United Kingdom. For 2014/15 those estimated savings are £87m and in 2015/16 they will rise to £114m.</p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46466/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46466/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the likely reduction to the block grant for Northern Ireland in the current financial year arising from lack of progress on welfare reform.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","194898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46467","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>On 27 March the Government published a Review of the Dormant Bank and Building Society Accounts Act 2008, which set out the Government's view on the existing schemes set up in the legislation.</p><p> </p><p>The Government currently has no plans to use funds from unclaimed life insurance policies, but keeps all policy under review.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46467/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46467/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what future plans the Government has to utilise funds from the unclaimed life policies or dormant bank accounts.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","194907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46469","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>There have been no miscalculations as a result of any errors in the calculation methodology. 11 cases have, however, been recalculated as a result of new information supplied by the policyholder.</p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46469/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46469/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the number of compensation cases which have been miscalculated by the Equitable Life Payment Scheme.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","194850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46470","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-08","<p>Of the 495 cases submitted to the Independent Review Panel to date, 145 were classified as being about the level of payment received.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46470/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46470/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many appeals have been made to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme on the level of compensation offered since the scheme began making payments.","false","Biography information for Sir Graham Brady","Altrincham and Sale West","Mr Graham Brady","194827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46471","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>Data on vacant dwellings by tenure and district, including Rossendale and Blackburn with Darwen, can be found in live table 615 which is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-dwelling-stock-including-vacants" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-dwelling-stock-including-vacants</a></p><p>This table brings together figures on vacant dwellings in England drawn from several separately published sources.</p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46471/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46471/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many empty homes there are in (a) Rossendale and (b) Darwen.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","194838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46472","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>All results are approved within each local authority's internal audit arrangements and under the statutory authority of the Chief Executive. My Department then undertakes a verification process on a sample of claims made.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46472/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46472/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how self-reported data from local authorities on the Troubled Families programme is audited.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46473","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-30","<p> </p><p>TELL MAMA is the first service to record and monitor anti-Muslim hatred incidents and support victims. DCLG provided initial start-up grant funding to TELL MAMA of £395,500 between January 2012 and September 2013. TELL MAMA has subsequently received Big Lottery funding of £255,450 over two years from October 2013.</p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-04-30T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46473/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46473/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much grant-in-aid his Department has provided to Tell MAMA since May 2010; and what further funding he expects to provide.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46474","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-30","<p> </p><p>This Government has been clear about its intention to devolve power, responsibility and decision-making down to the lowest possible level. This vision underpins significant elements of our policy agenda which are transferring power and freedom to both local councils and communities, some of which are noted below.</p><p>Nearly 1,000 assets of community value have been listed and we have helped 150 organisations to acquire a community asset or obtain significant investment towards doing so. 16 local campaigns for new parish councils are being supported covering local populations of more than half a million people. Over 100 new Our Place areas are starting work within their communities to transform neighbourhood level service delivery. Community share issues have raised over £24 million for community ventures.</p><p>Nearly 800 neighbourhood planning areas have been designated, and all 13 plans which have so far reached referenda have passed with significant majorities in favour.</p><p>Local authorities are now required to pass a proportion of Community Infrastructure Levy funding to local communities so that they can directly see the benefit of local development.</p><p>Over 2013-15 £14 million has been made available for community groups to develop their proposals for Community Right to Build orders or to progress community-led development. Groups can develop their ideas on the development that they want and need in their areas.Applications for this funding continue to rise with around 60 applications received.</p><p>In April 2014 four new combined authorities were established, on the request of the councils concerned. These will support the councils to collaborate and work jointly across the wider functional economic areas on economic development, regeneration and transport to support economic growth in the areas of South Yorkshire, West Yorkshire, Greater Merseyside and Durham, Northumberland and Tyne and Wear.</p><p>The Government wants local authorities to be more transparent and accountable to local people for how they spend money, deliver services and take decisions. We will shortly be publishing a revised local authority transparency code extending the breadth of data that local authorities must publish and will make regulations to make publication of certain data a legal requirement. Also, Regulations which will allow members of the public including professional journalists to film, photograph, audio-record and use social media to report the proceedings of meetings of local government bodies, and to access documents relating to decisions made by officers under delegation from their local government bodies, are now before Parliament.</p><p>Under the business rates retention scheme local authorities now directly retain nearly £11 billion of business rates, instead of returning it to Whitehall.</p><p>The Government has also reformed the outdated council housing finance system with the introduction of self-financing in 2012. This has given the 167 council landlords greater freedoms and the ability to plan for the long term to better meet the needs of their tenants and local area.</p><p><em>HomeSwap</em> Direct - the national home swap scheme which increases opportunities for social tenants wishing to move through mutual exchange – was launched in October 2011 and since then tenants have made over 18 million searches of ‘partner' data.</p><p>Social landlords are now free to match the length of tenancy to the needs of the household and to use their social housing stock in a way which best meets the needs of their local area. Councils have the freedom to decide who qualifies for social housing in their area and to find alternative solutions for those who do not qualify.</p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-04-30T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46474/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46474/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent progress he has made on the localism agenda; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","194875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46475","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Monday 7 April 2014]</em></p><p>The number of staff that left the Department on (a) voluntary redundancy and (b) compulsory redundancy terms from May 2010 to March 2014 is set out below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>May 2010 to March 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Compulsory Redundancy</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Voluntary Severance or Redundancy</p></td><td><p>522</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>530</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>None of these staff (i) received special severance payments or (ii) were subject to compromise agreements.</p><p>Exit figures through 2010 – 2012 reflect the completion of the Department's major restructuring programme. Our departmental audited annual accounts for the core Department show that total staff costs fell from £216 million in 2009-10 to £99 million in 2012-13, a reduction of 54% in cash terms, or a saving of £117 million a year. The number of staff has been reduced from 3,781 full-time equivalent in 2009-10 to 1,681 in 2012-13, a reduction of 56%.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46475/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46475/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46475/answer/previousversion/5030","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many staff have (a) taken voluntary redundancy or (b) been made compulsorily redundant from his Department since May 2010; and how many of these (i) received special severance payments or (ii) were subject to compromise agreements.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46476","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Monday 7 April 2014]</em></p><p>On 25 March, Departmental officials wrote to the Chief Executives of every principal local authority in England, advising how the Secretary of State is minded to exercise his powers to direct compliance with the Code of Recommended Practice on local Authority Publicity. On the same day, I wrote individually to the Leaders of the Royal Borough of Greenwich, London Borough of Hackney, Newham Council, Nottingham City Council, Tower Hamlets Council and the London Borough of Waltham Forest. Without prejudicing any formal consideration by the Secretary of State, I observed that there were suggestions that those councils in particular might not be complying with the Code of Recommended Practice on Local Authority Publicity. I suggested that prior to the Secretary of State's new powers for directing compliance with the Code on publicity coming on-stream at the end of March, they take steps to ensure that their council is in complete compliance with the provisions of the Code. Those letters were copied where applicable to the Leaders of the opposition in those authorities.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46476/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46476/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46476/answer/previousversion/5032","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, to which local authorities he has written about their compliance with the Publicity Code asking them to take steps to ensure complete compliance with that Code; and whether each of these letters was copied to the Leader of the Opposition of the local authority.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46477","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-07","<p> </p><p>I refer the rt. hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statement made today by my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government (Eric Pickles).</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46477/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46477/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the use of public money by the Mayor of Tower Hamlets to fund third sector organisations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46479","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-10","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government is currently in discussions with the Local Government Association on this matter.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46479/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46479/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the financial effect on local authorities when the single tier state pension is introduced in 2016-17 and local authorities no longer receive a national insurance rebate from the contracting out of pensions.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","194998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46480","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-07","<p> </p><p>The main consideration in the recovery of wind turbine appeals is the potential impact of the development on the surrounding area, in the particular circumstances of each appeal and its location. The generation capacity of the appeal is not a driver in the decision on whether or not the appeal should be recovered.</p><p>As I said in my earlier answer my Department does not centrally hold details of the generation capacity of wind turbine appeals.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","194930","2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46480/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46480/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2014, Official Report, column 533W, on wind power, how his Department makes decisions on planning and recoveries without centrally holding the capacity of energy schemes.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","194931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46481","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-07","<p> </p><p>My Department has not made any estimates in this area but I do encourage local authorities to take full advantage of the efficiencies that electronic ways of working can bring.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46481/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46481/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of line of business and desktop applications in local government.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","194949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46482","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-04-07","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is the lead Department on policy and funding for buses.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46482/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46482/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effects of reductions in shire county council bus subsidies on the opportunities for social interaction of elderly and disabled people.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46483","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-05-01","<p> </p><p>I will provide a comprehensive answer to the rt. hon. Member in due course. We are currently gathering historic files, given some of the information requested predates the establishment of the National Planning Casework Unit in 2011.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46483/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46483/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he expects to answer question No. 191956 tabled by the Rt hon. Member for Leeds Central on 13 March 2014.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","194894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46489","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-08","<p>Training of UK personnel in the six countries identified has not involved unmanned aircraft actively engaged in operations. Unmanned aircraft system (UAS) training has only ever occurred in non-operational environments, specifically the countries listed in my previous answer on 27 March 2014. Army UAS actively engaged in operations have always been, and continue to be, remotely piloted solely by fully trained personnel operating on the ground in the country in which the operation is active. This has only been in Iraq and Afghanistan.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46489/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46489/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 27 March 2014, Official Report, columns 322-3W, on unmanned air vehicles, whether the training of UK personnel in the six countries identified has involved unmanned aircraft actively engaged in operations.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","195003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46490","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-29","<p>RAF Remotely Piloted Air System (RPAS) personnel are based at RAF Waddington and Creech Air Force Base, Nevada.</p><p> </p><p>RAF Personnel are from the following branches or specialisation:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Branch/Specialisation</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Pilot</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sensor Operator</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mission Intelligence Coordinator</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Operations</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Engineer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Administration</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>RAF RPAS Squadrons can also include personnel from the Royal Navy, Royal Marines and Army.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-04-29T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46490/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46490/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 17 March 2014, Official Report, column 490W, on the Royal Air Force, if he will provide details of (a) each base at which RAF personnel from the Remotely Piloted Air System division are stationed and (b) the branch and specialisation of every such person.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","195004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46491","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-09","<p>To date, there have been no discussions with the Government of Afghanistan about the future basing of UK unmanned aircraft systems in Afghanistan after 2014.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46491/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46491/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has had any discussions with the government of Afghanistan concerning future basing of UK unmanned aircraft systems in that country after 2014.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","194985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46492","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no record of any aircraft carrying MQ-1 Predators air-to-air refuelling over the UK, or landing at RAF Mildenhall to refuel, over the last three years.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46492/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46492/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 20 March 2014, Official Report, column 703W, on RAF Mildenhall, whether his Department maintains records of all MQ-1 Predators carried in aircraft which refuel in the air or by landing at RAF Mildenhall; and whether he will disclose the date of each such flight over the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","194999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46493","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) has no record of receiving the letter from the hon. Member for Cardiff South and Penarth. The MOD requested a copy of the letter on 3 April 2014 and will respond shortly.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46493/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46493/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Cardiff South and Penarth of 23 December 2013, regarding a review of a discharge from the British Army.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","194955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46494","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-08","<p>I am withholding details of the locations at which Taranis flight trials have taken place for the purpose of safeguarding national security. The Ministry of Defence has no plans to create weapons that operate without human control. Trained members of the Armed Forces will always be involved in the command and control of unmanned air systems.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46494/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46494/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether there has been any testing (a) in Southern Australia and (b) elsewhere of the ability of the Taranis system to identify or strike targets autonomously.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","194956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46495","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-07","<p>Information on spending on defence procurement in financial year 2013-14 will be available once the audit of defence expenditure in that year has been completed; we are due to report our 2013-14 financial performance in our Annual Report and Accounts before the House rises for the summer recess. Information for April to September 2013 was published in the Ministry of Defence (MOD)'s Mid Year Report on 24 January 2014, available at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministry-of-defence-mid-year-progress-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministry-of-defence-mid-year-progress-report</a></p><p>The MOD does not routinely record information on the geographic location of its supply chain.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46495/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46495/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department spend was in total in 2013-14 on defence procurement; and what proportion of that total was spent in the (a) UK, (b) EU and (c) rest of the world.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","194941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46496","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-07","<p>This information will be available once the 2014-15 Main Supply Estimates have been laid before the House, which is currently planned for the end of April 2014.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46496/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46496/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-02","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department plans to spend on defence procurement in 2014-15 as a proportion of the overall departmental budget.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","194943"
