"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46174","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-07","<p>There is no requirement for someone using the employee shareholder employment status to register with any government department or agency. Therefore, Government does not hold numbers.</p><p> </p><p>The employee shareholder employment status is a voluntary option that people may wish to consider using.</p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46174/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46174/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-01","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people have applied to be an employee shareholder under the Government's Shares for Rights Scheme to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","194810"
